HEADWORD: Suprahepatic
<hw>Su`pra*he*pat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated over, or on the dorsal side of, the liver; -- applied to
the branches of the hepatic veins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

